# ================================
# üìù CONFIGURATION NOTES
# ================================

# REQUIRED VARIABLES:
# - DISCORD_TOKEN: Get from Discord Developer Portal
# - CLIENT_ID: Your Discord application ID
# - DATABASE_URL: PostgreSQL connection string
# - ADMIN_USER_ID: Your Discord user ID for admin commands

# REDIS CONFIGURATION:
# - Redis is OPTIONAL - bot works perfectly without it
# - With Redis: Faster canvas generation and caching
# - Without Redis: Uses in-memory fallback cache
# - Railway users: Use REDISHOST/REDISPORT variables
# - Other hosting: Use REDIS_HOST/REDIS_PORT variables

# TIER ROLES:
# - Tier roles provide increased daily XP caps
# - Users with tier roles can gain more XP per day
# - Tier roles stack with regular level roles
# - Configure as many or as few as you need

# VOICE XP SETTINGS:
# - VOICE_MIN_MEMBERS: Minimum users in channel for XP
# - VOICE_ANTI_AFK: Reduce XP for muted/deafened users
# - VOICE_MUTE_EXEMPT: Users/roles exempt from AFK penalty

# DAILY RESET:
# - DAILY_RESET_HOUR_EDT: Hour in EDT (0-23)
# - DAILY_RESET_MINUTE_EDT: Minute (0-59)
# - Example: 0 and 30 = 12:30 AM EDT daily reset

# LEVEL ROLES:
# - Automatically assigned when users reach levels
# - Bot removes lower level roles when assigning higher ones
# - Requires "Manage Roles" permission
# - Bot's role must be higher than roles it manages

# XP MULTIPLIERS:
# - XP_MULTIPLIER: Global XP multiplier (affects all sources)
# - Individual XP boost roles can be configured via /settings

# LOGGING:
# - XP_LOG_CHANNEL: Channel for detailed XP activity logs
# - Individual log types can be enabled/disabled
# - Includes daily cap progress and tier information
